cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SY

The paper deals with game theory and decision making in stochastic environments, which are topics covered by cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of the window mechanism and the development of a generic approach for window-based objectives also involve algorithmic and computational aspects, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
